      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-lot screws and rods, lot-traceable to device master record. Sample size provides adequate statistical power for mean comparison at 80% power, alpha=0.05. Both laboratories used identical assembly torque specifications per F1717."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must span the range of loading scenarios relevant to the COU or deficiencies must be documented.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single compression-bending load angle per F1717 protocol. The COU description acknowledges this limitation; only one test condition was evaluated, yielding achieved gradation 2 against a required gradation 3. This known gap is documented as a credibility shortfall."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
