    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the FEA modeling framework for the non-cannulated pedicle screw COU based on satisfactory output comparison results (E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs, relative error < 10%) and adequate assessment of 11 of 13 V&V 40 factors. Two factors (numerical solver error, use error) were noted as not assessed and characterized as beyond the scope of the current submission; the team judged that default solver settings and experienced analyst protocols provided sufficient practical assurance. The test conditions shortfall (achieved gradation 2 vs. required 3) was acknowledged. Overall credibility was deemed sufficient for a medium-risk, medium-consequence COU at modelRiskLevel 3.",
